      <section eId="sec_HRULE-15-9">
        <num>HRULE 15.9</num>
        <heading>Section </heading>
        <subsection eId="HRULE-15-9__subsec_1">
          <num>(1)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Conduct all hearings as public hearings, and only after informing the member in writing of the date and time of each meeting held for the purpose.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="HRULE-15-9__subsec_2">
          <num>(2)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Invite the member who is the subject of the hearing to attend all meetings of the committee in person and to be accompanied by legal counsel, or to be represented at the hearings by legal counsel of his choice if he is unable to be present.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="HRULE-15-9__subsec_3">
          <num>(3)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Afford the member full opportunity to be heard and to present witnesses on his behalf and extend to him the right to confront and to cross examine witnesses called by the committee.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="HRULE-15-9__subsec_4">
          <num>(4)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Advise the member immediately of the date and time of each meeting, in cases where the committee adjourns prior to completing its work and submitting its report to the House of Representatives.
HR 4, 1st Ex. Sess., 1986.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=113282</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
